				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Epic Quest Balance - a message from Sony<a name="66481"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 12 04 9:50 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well.. i can only comment on what i read, cos i have not attempted the DN fights myself..
<br />

<br />
But from what i read, it IS completely out of whack if compared to most(all) of the other epic 1.5's around.
<br />

<br />
My main is a Ranger.. Ranger 1.5 epic includes some foraging and soloable mobs to make some weapons that &quot;capture&quot; a animal to get its blood. Making of theese weapons require a skill of 15 fletching.. i am, as many other rangers, a GM fletcher with 250 + mod. Even tho the skill is only 15, it at least uses a &quot;ranger-typical&quot; tradeskill.. Imo inline with a class spesific quest.
<br />
After that i duoed 3 of the mobs.. me 66 ranger and a 55 druid on second computer. For last of the &quot;captured&quot; mobs i got help from a 67 chanter in the guild.
<br />
After that, there is 2 lvl 64 or so mobs that need to be killed. Also did that with 3 (Me, druid and chanter). 
<br />
Then some turnins.. and i am ready for 3 final battles requiring around 4-5 groups for me.
<br />

<br />
My guild is not in elementals yet (Missing RZ atm). We do however have EP/Time+ geared people, but they are not majority of the guild.
<br />

<br />
The 3 last fights happens in Bloodfields (Druid/wiz ports aviable), Natimbi (druid/wiz port aviable) and Ruined city of dranik..
<br />

<br />
So.. 2 of the 3 final TOUGH fights are easily accessible with porters too..
<br />

<br />
Compare that with Bard epic.. Honestly, the DN part should be skipped, or tuned down to be 1 groupable at MAX(Non EP geared). Tune the dragons to be MAX 2 groupable, and you suddenly have 2-3 fights left that require guild help. This would be inline with the other epics.. as things are today, it is WAY out of whack compared.
<br />
</span></td>
