			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Epic Quest Balance - a message from Sony<a name="66484"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 12 04 10:10 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>As of this morning, the official Sony response is that they have fixed the Kithicor bug and the DN &quot;bug&quot; with too many guards spawning with patches to those zones yesterday.  This is the e-mail I had in the in-box this morning from Brenlo:
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I am very happy that you find the current flow of information helpful.  We, unfortunately, did not push the changes to the Kithicor Forest live on Friday, they are live as of this correspondence, along with the changes to Dragon's Necropolis.  
<br />
 
<br />
With Necropolis, the NPCs were spawning incorrectly, in that too many were spawning and they were not despawning correctly.  This resulted in more NPCs being involved in the encounter than we had planned.  This should now be corrected.  Please let me know of any new feedback related to the changes we made today.
<br />
 
<br />
As to comparisons between the steps in the bard epic and other epic quests, we feel that we have parity between the quests.  We are comfortable with where they are currently.  However I will bring your concerns to the team for consideration and should we come to any conclusions that involve a change in the quest, I will let you know.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I've been telling a lot of my guildies that there will be no changes to the structure of the quests and I have been telling them that for two weeks.  Sony has no problem, after you present them with evidence, in admitting there is a bug and then attempting to fix that bug.  Sometimes, they still can't find the answer after three years but they at least admit there's a bug.  However, in EverQuest, one thing that simply does not exist is a design flaw.  They NEVER make a mistake in developmental design.  So despite the fact that the bard epic requires three to seven times the man-hours in group/guild help that several other epics require, we have &quot;parity&quot; between epics.  Because Sony cannot possibly make a mistake in design.
<br />

<br />
I give the team at SOE props for fixing the bugs and communicating with me on this one.  But their stubborn refusal to even consider the possibility that their design is flawed on these quests is troubling.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
