				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Epic Quest Balance - a message from Sony<a name="66488"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 12 04 10:19 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I am clearly mising something here. The 2.2 mod is nice,especially when grouped, but how is it going to be especially helpful on raids? On raids I either debuff, play resists, do mana, play MA songs or just do group songs and melee (oops forgot pulling). For the first 2 of these I use a drum. If we need more regen with mana I use a lute. Several of us have the 2.0 singing mod drop from Sarryn in torment so if we need increased singing mod for MA songs this is a very margina increase. If I am in a dps grp this will give a small extra increase to attack. The click effect lasts for one minute and gives about 5 to 10 extra dps from the folks I have chatted with. So, in summation it seems to me that this is a weapon with really nice stats for a pre-Time bard but its effects provide minimal benefit to a guild. A nice upgrade for the bard who only groups but even there it still seems lacking compared to other epics. (Yes, I did the math and its downright depressing to think that I would have to drag people to 8 raids for such a small increase in AC and resists).
<br />

<br />
Rinludar</span></td>
