			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Epic Quest Balance - a message from Sony<a name="66524"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 12 04 1:24 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Interesting feedback from Sony.  I can understand how they feel our epic is balanced, in a convoluted kind of way.  If you use strategies, and don't go in undermanned, our epic is probably one of the fastest to do.  A little too fast in my opinion.  If you hit the bazaar for diamonds, get the enchanted bars of velium, and farm the dragorn blood, you can do your epic in one night.  
<br />

<br />
Lots of other classes have frustrating, time consuming camps.  My pally friend was on hour 22 of camping Screambringers in Barindu.  This requires less than a group, but you have to keep people there for a long time.  I don't want to spoil too much, but I will try to put our epic into perspective:
<br />

<br />
- Gathering bones is simple for a bard.  All three ground spawns can be picked up solo.  All the mercs can be chant kited solo.  Both Excavator and Tarm are trioable with tank, bard, healer.  It's up to the bard to get Tarm solo, but easily doable with our tools.
<br />

<br />
- First DN fight is very easy if you set up right.  I know some people have said that they got the hall adds when the pulled Vasthon, but I have done this twice, never saw that.  The three zombies are kited, leaving Vasthon/Draco.  Vaston is a sissy, draco is tougher.  Every priest class has AE heals now, use them.  The ramp sounds worse than it is.  Just keep everyone aware to move out of range if you getting beat on too hard.  Really the Draco's atk rating must be very low.  Maybe 5pct of his hits were for max,according to the MT that did it.
<br />

<br />
- Second DN fight is the tough part.  I do agree this could use some tuning.  However, is SoE's note to Steppy is accurate, then maybe each lich only has one minion, which would put this fight back in line.  This is our big epic raid fight, which many classes have (Clr in WL, Wiz in SD and WoS).  It sucks that our raid is at the beginning, which roadblocks progression, but it is what it is.
<br />

<br />
- 4 dragons scale in difficulty.  From my experience, Swamp, Mountain, Plains, Forest.  Swamp and mountain are a simple tank fight that is just a strugle to maintain mana levels, depending on gear.  Plains was tougher, since the AE requires more healing.  A warrior is best to use defensive; the dragons don't hit hard and can be killed before defensive drops.  A note on Forest, do not melee.  It is wasteful of the healers mana, just use range damage only.  Bring rangers and casters for fastest killing.  I had 3 Trueshot rangers, this dragon dropped faster than any of the others.
<br />

<br />
- Bazaar farming and blood gathering is self explanatory.
<br />

<br />
- Kithicor fight isn't bad.  I setup at WC zone line, which was probably wrong in hindsight.  He moves east to west, which means we were chasing him down.  We also did it at night, which meant lots of trash adds from undead.  He stays on the trail, just hail him twice, then have people pick up the adds.  The mobs hit weak, like 300 or 400.  I had one warrior, one pally, 2 ranger tanks for this.  Just systematically use assist to kill them quick.  Keep an eye out for named thief, he will add like a normal shade.  Mez or tank mez the normal shades, get whole raid on thief.  Shades depop when thief is killed.
<br />

<br />
- Torment is also easy.  You basically wont resist the AE silence, so hide the healers and casters.  Otherwise, straight tank fight, no damage AE's.  
<br />

<br />
This is our whole epic 1.5.  Compare this to some other classes, and see how very short ours is.  In exchange, we require more multi-group assistance.  I don't think this is bad, just different.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
