				<td colspan="2"><span>The more I study it, the more I think Kanarian is right.  Instead of 5 or 6 long, boring farming camps we can do solo or with a couple of patient friends, we get 4 dragon fights.  I think our epic requires more people to assist us than any other epic.  However, it DOES demand a lot less time than most of them.  Sony probably sees this as parity in terms of some abstract quanta called &quot;challenge.&quot;  What they fail to realize, and this is universal - not just specific to the epic - is that for some players at their level of the game, getting together 30 elemental-geared friends for even one fight is far more challenging than 30 hours of camping farmed mobs with a friend or two.  I will get my epic, but it will take months because the resources available -- my guild -- are going to be spread way too thin over the weeks ahead doing 60-some epics and maintaining our normal raid schedule.  We have a couple of people already epic because they could do 90% of theirs without the involvement of a guild.  And this is where the lack of &quot;parity&quot; really exists.  Sony's evaulations that X amount of farmin = Y amount of raid fights is skewed heavily toward the notion that something like six hours of framing for a necro solo is equal to one hour of gathering a 30 person raid and executing it.  The fact is, the solo farming is significantly easier, just more time consuming.  Some of us have time to spare but getting the manpower together for these fights will strain our relationships with guild and friends, especially right now when everyone else in the guild needs raids done for epics too.</span></td>
