				<td colspan="2"><span>The way our guild resolved this problem Steppy is to dedicate one night a week to Epics.  You get charged a certain loot value in exchange for renting the guild's time.  We got 7 Epic raid fights done last Friday. The rules are that you come prepared with everything needed to trigger, and know the general event.  
<br />

<br />
We did 2 Wiz fights in Scarelt Desert, the WL event for clerics twice, my DN2 fight, and a few others.  It goes surprisingly fast, and people are paying loot points, so you get raid credit.  
<br />

<br />
With regards to parity between few multi group fights vs. long solo/group farming camps, it is a double edged sword.  People in a raiding guild do not have tons of free time, especially since some of the camps are contested (had fun in Quinimi racing others for Spiritmasters for pallies).  On the other hand, people not in a raid guild do not have access to a large roster of people to call on.  
<br />

<br />
What I have seen on my server is akin to a /openraid channel, but for epics.  People join the channel and help, then in return get help from others.  People not in a guild act like only guilds can gather groups of people, but this isn't true.  
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
