				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Epic Quest Balance - a message from Sony<a name="66587"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 12 04 5:17 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>My two bit observations to all of this - keeping in mind that I'm still relatively early in the process.
<br />

<br />
My expectations for Epic 1.5 - as set by Sony - was that a guild such as mine would be able to do all of them. A solid turn out for a raid including bots for us is 18-20. I expected to be somewhat stretched to do it, and to quite likely have to wait until a good hunk of us were level 70 with some degree of average oow gear (with our numbers, elementals is not something we'll ever see). This, to me, fit inline of the notion of some soloing, some group encounters, and perhaps a few *small* raids. By definition, the fact that it was labled as not being the one for raiding guild members means that you can't expect 30+ toons to show up, nor can you expect time+ or even elemental gear IMHO (though, looking at some of the very obtainable OoW drops, maybe you can expect elemental).
<br />

<br />
Some have complained that 1.5 is underpowered. Personally, I agree that the ratio is just a tad weak relative to other 1.5's (hoping for the improvement there), but it otherwise seems pretty spot on for the level of player it's targeted at. The reason for the raiding guild bard to go get it is that is is part of the larger 2.0 epic - that's the one I expect to be simply awesome (much as 1.0 was back in Kunark). You simply can't put epic 2.0 expectations on 1.5. I honestly never expect to see 2.0 - it's meant for raiding guilds, and that's not where I'm ever going to be. For me, it's &quot;Thank you SOE for remembering the little guy&quot; this time around.
<br />

<br />
Now, that begs the question: &quot;What did we really wind up with?&quot; From what I can see early in things, the fights seem all to be reasonable except DN2. The jury is still out on just how hard that one will be after the fix. What I'm after out of all these encounters is that they are doable by 18 or less people equipped with the gear/spells available to the &quot;common player&quot; in OoW. Level 70 needed for everyone? Fine, that's fair. Need those nice BF, PG, WoS, etc. drops in your equipment list? OK, cool - I'm jiggy with it. What I was seeing out of DN2 was something not doable without raw headcount, and that was my tweak on it (it's worth noting that SK's definitely have a fight that is headcount dependent too).
<br />

<br />
Stay tuned - I hope to be at DN2 this week.</span></td>
