				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Epic Quest Balance - a message from Sony<a name="66593"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 12 04 5:47 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">The more I study it, the more I think Kanarian is right. Instead of 5 or 6 long, boring farming camps we can do solo or with a couple of patient friends, we get 4 dragon fights. I think our epic requires more people to assist us than any other epic. However, it DOES demand a lot less time than most of them. </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Steppy, this is incorrect. Some bards may have the money and luck to buy the planes drops they need to complete their epic, but others will not. Therefore, they will be required to camp these items with friends. (Most can not be soloed well.) Additionally, we are required to camp Dragorn Blood. Which does not always drop at a fast rate. We by no means have the chalenge of our fights off-set by not needing to camp drops. 
<br />

<br />
There are a few other things that come up for me after reading this thread.
<br />

<br />
1. Getting people to DN is not a huge time sink. Port to CS and run through SG and your almost right at the DN zone-in. Any player that can't get through SG might not be up to doing the DN fights. (Though folks seem dumb enough to trigger the bone traps as they run in. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" /> ) No way does it take two hours to get there. Additionally, the last SK fight is in WW so we're not alone.
<br />

<br />
Personally, the hardest place to get a raid force to is the monk's 7th Hammer fight. I don't know about others, but not many players I know completed all six PoJ trials. So now your not just asking a few players to take the time to get flagged for this fight, your asking a whole raid force to take time to get a very old and unused PoP flag. I'm not going to complain about asking them to run to DN after this.
<br />

<br />
2. The effort to complete these epics are by no means equal. The last fight for the Nec. and SK. are about as tough as our first shade fight in DN. The rougue and warrior final fights are slightly more chalenging. The BL and ranger one looks to be a slightly more simple then of last DN fight. The cleric final fight is very hard and I don't see a casual player doing this fight. 
<br />

<br />
Therefore, I don't think the fights themselves are more chalenging then all other class epic, I just think that we have twice as many that require raids.
<br />

<br />
The bards epic 1.5 is very doable. Will a truely casual player be able to complete it. I really don't think so. But the bard 1.5 epic is not the must have that the first bard epic was.
<br />

<br />
Gaylon Dragonsong
<br />
Ascending Dawn
<br />
RZ</span></td>
