				<td colspan="2"><span>Total money spent in bazaar:  8404p.  Money spent on Velium bars: 2kish.  10K is not a large sum of money for a 65+ player (and this is the req level for epic, so this is fair).  Feel free to camp the actual parts for the diamonds, but I can tell you it is much faster to earn plat than to gather all of the drops.  
<br />

<br />
Dragorn blood is easy to get in WoS.  Just ooc for it while grouping near dragorns.  I got 4 bloods from mobs I killed, 4 from people offering it.  Be very sure not to train though, I was denied one blood because the group that got it was trained earlier by another bard.  
<br />

<br />
7th hammer flagging is fast to do.  My guild is already doing this.  Take one group through all 6 in about an hour.  Yes it sucks for monks to have to push people through, but this is how you get help for your own epic.  Get flagged, help a few monks, and now you have some additional bodies for your own fights.  
<br />

<br />
It is easy for us to complain about the number of raids our epic takes, but check the forum on the original Epic, and look at the multiple threads on Phinny kills to backbones ratio.  The epic must be hard, or it isn't epic.  Every class has some point of the epic that is a headache.  Necros are going nuts camping an uncommon drop off an uncommon mob in PoI.  Good luck if another necro is hunting it too.  We have zero competition for our epic mobs.  
<br />

<br />
Yes, the DN2 fight is a bit too much.  I suspect that the problem in the script was too many minions per Lich, and this may get tuned down to one per lich.  This means you will have to mez 4 blue con mobs, and off tank 3 while kiling liches.  Further, as you kill the liches, the minions despawn, so it gets easier as you go along in the script.  
<br />

<br />
The Vasthon/Draco part of DN2 is not too bad if you are smart about it.  A few healers with MGB heals and group heals, warrior with defensive, and ranged DPS make this simple.  You just have to use tactics on this fight.  
<br />

