Just not true.  I thought this same way until I did the epic.  The DN2 fight yes; but most everyone agrees it is out of balance.  The other fights just aren't.  Two dragons are one groupable, one is 2 groupable, one is three groupable.  I had 18 people for Kith and Torment, had zero deaths, so I could have done it with less.  Half were Time+, but other half were crappy geared bots, so I would call it about EP time average.  
<br />

<br />
As for solo stuff, the 8 bloods is our tedious solo camp.  You can get them in any OoW zone, including DS and NC.  I tried soloing for it in NC, but it was just too slow. If you enjoy endless hours of chant kiting, you can solo this part.  Grouping not required, just faster.  
<br />

<br />
I think that people complaining about the difficulty of it should consider other class epics, aside from Shaman and Necro (I think that these are too easy, but not really looking for a flame fest).  Clerics have to camp 4 lore random drops in Ferubi.  Crap exp at 70, and I was there 5 hours.  We have 9 more clerics to get epics for, so they have to gather help for this, and they are envious of how fast and not tedious ours is.
<br />

<br />
The grass is always greener:  classes with long rare camps want short fast fights (even if it means multi-group).  We have that, yet are complaining that we don't have more long rare camps.  I think we should accept what we got, and work wth it.  You will have no problems getting help with your epic if you do a lot of 5 hour Ferubi camps.  Plus, you will appreciate rolling through triggered fight after triggered fight after many a long rare camp.
