				<td colspan="2"><span>Thanks for the efforts Steppy, I certainly appreciate it.
<br />

<br />
I, for one, dont think the epic is overly unbalanced to be honest.  I'm in Gwenwyvar's guild, and the only thing that stopped us doing the DN encounter 4 times was the lockout timer.  THATS the biggest blocker from what I see.
<br />

<br />
If anything, the lockout timer on the 4+ group events (for all epics) should be removed.  Its hard enough getting people there once let alone 4 or 5 times.  Use the right tactics, the 2nd DN fight is a 5-7 min fight.
<br />

<br />
The entire epic 1.5 is very straightforward, same as our original one.  Straightforward doesnt mean easy, just uncomplicated.  And if you think your tactics out a little, the supposedly hard fights are not as hard as you think.
<br />

<br />
It IS a Time level weapon.  It's allready been confirmed its being changed to 24/22, which is exactly the same ratio as the Songblade of the Eternal - a bards Time weapon.  It's not something that a pre elemental person should find easy to get.  And its still gettable for pre elementals if you think things out.
<br />

<br />
Use some common sense and think the encounters out a little, zerg rushing isnt always the answer.  DN, pre target the mezable mobs, and take out the liches whos minions cant be mez'd first.  I also suggest a /hidecorpse all hotkey in case you get spider adds...
<br />

<br />
JPF dragon, use ranged tactics.  Those are the 2 hard fights.  The rest are relatively straightforward.  And for a weapon thats the same ratio as SotE, it sure takes a lot less people to kill the needed mobs.</span></td>
