				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Epic Quest Balance - a message from Sony<a name="66816"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 14 04 1:04 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I too feel that our epic is out of balance for pre-elemental bards aka the Casual Player. I am what I would consider an elemental bard and I think that the 4 dragons yielding no loot to those that help you just plain stinks. It doesn't help the fact that not only do we have to call on those same people for 4 dragons but to call on even more for the 2nd step in our epic, if you follow the progression correctly, and then again 2 more times for the fight in kithicor and the final fight in torment. The DN2 fight is too dificult for the chance that 1 chest may or may not spawn and that (from my observation) would take between 30 and 40 of the people from my guild (similarily geared as myself) to complete successfully. Take the cleric final battle as an example with 24 people similarily geared to myself we won. It wasn't pretty, in the end the skeleton adds were kited off and everyone was rezzed and we ported out, but it was doable with what I would consider a mini-raid. The bard epic requires 4-5 mini-raids, 2 2-3 group encounters, 1 1 groupable encounter, and 1 full blown raid (2nd step mind you) to get an item that is decent (post 10/13/04 patch) and probably useable up until Time when Songblade becomes an option and will undoubtedly do more dps due to the damage bonus being applied more often. I am not saying it is impossible to achieve for a elemental guild, because its not, but it does require that bard to basically steal a day of raiding to drag enough people out to DN to get an intermediate piece in the epic.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
